    "Performance ComparisonTable I summarizes the performance metrics, parameter efficiency, and training characteristics of the four PEFT methods: Table I: Comparison of PEFT Methods on PUBMEDQA Method Accuracy F1 Score Trainable Parameters Parameter Efficiency Class Discriminat -ion Adapter (Pfeiffer) 79.0% 0.79 2.1M 1.89% Strong LoRA 51.5% 0.23 0.297M 0.27% Poor Prompt Tuning 51.5% 0.23 9, 987 0.009% None Prefix Tuning 51.5% 0.23 14.8M 11.9% None B.",
    "Detailed Analysis Performance Across Methods: The adapter approach significantly outperformed other PEFT methods, achieving 79% accuracy with good discrimination between classes.",
    "In contrast, LoRA, Prompt Tuning, and Prefix Tuning all converged to predicting only the majority class (\"yes\"), resulting in identical performance metrics (51.5% accuracy and 0.23 F1 score).",
    "Parameter Efficiency: Prompt Tuning achieved the highest parameter efficiency, requiring only 0.009% of the model's parameters, while Prefix Tuning unexpectedly had the lowest efficiency at 11.9%.",
    "LoRA demonstrated excellent efficiency at 0.3% while Adapters used a moderate 1.89% of parameters."
